  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;Title&gt;Wear a Mask Please&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I visited the blood clinic on Thursday 7th January 2021 around 10am. I arrived very early for my appointment so had a long wait. No problem at all there. 

During my wait, I became aware of a volunteer who was standing and chatting with various members of staff for some considerable time. The problem was that they kept removing their mask. They were laughing and joking, all lovely to see, but all risky behaviour at the moment with no mask. There were patients arriving for various clinics having to walk right past. 

Volunteers are a great asset and they deserve praise for the help they are giving but at the moment, without a mask, this person is a risk to patients, staff and themselves. Perhaps gentle reminders would make things safer for all. &lt;/CommentText&gt;
